== Misinformation based on an old, outdated, and improper source ==

"the minority party of the Cherokees gave its allegiance to the Confederacy, while originally the majority party went for the North." Is placed on the top of the page on the first 100 words. This link http://www.civilwarhome.com/nativeamericans.htm also has a timestamp on the bottom of the page saying last updated in 2002.

Just thought id point out a few things

==Sourcing for claim in the lead==
I can't seem to find a ''reliable'' source that notes most Native Americans fought for the Confederacy. There are plenty of other, non-reliable source, however. For example, [http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/confederacy-signs-treaties-with-native-americans sources like this one]. I know there are academic books that point to this that I can try to dig up. Just wanted to make note of this all. [[User:DaltonCastle|DaltonCastle]] ([[User talk:DaltonCastle|talk]]) 05:12, 29 March 2016 (UTC)
